### Skill Assessment API Test File
### Use this with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@contentType = application/json

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/json

###

### Start New Session
# @name startSession
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/start
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "current_level": "Junior",
  "target_level": "Senior",
  "years_of_experience": 2.5,
  "primary_technologies": ["React", "JavaScript", "CSS", "HTML", "Git"],
  "additional_info": "Worked on e-commerce and dashboard projects"
}

###

### Continue Conversation (replace {session_id} with actual ID from previous response)
@sessionId = replace-with-actual-session-id

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/conversation/{{sessionId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "I recently worked on a React e-commerce application where I built the product listing, shopping cart, and checkout features. I used Redux for state management and integrated with Stripe API for payments."
}

###

### Get Conversation History
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/conversation/{{sessionId}}/history
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Self-Assessment Test
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/assessment/test/{{sessionId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Submit Self-Assessment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/assessment/submit/{{sessionId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "answers": [
    {
      "question_id": "replace-with-actual-question-id",
      "skill": "React",
      "answer": "Intermediate",
      "confidence_level": 4
    },
    {
      "question_id": "replace-with-actual-question-id",
      "skill": "JavaScript",
      "answer": "Advanced",
      "confidence_level": 4
    }
  ]
}

###

### Generate Gap Analysis Report
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gap-analysis/{{sessionId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Session Data
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/session/{{sessionId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### List All Sessions (Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions
Accept: application/json

###

### Delete Session
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/session/{{sessionId}}
Accept: application/json

###

